# Self-Directed Lab - ESP32
## Description

Information: What did you learn, and what was the source of the information?

- Watching a number of Youtube videos, I was able to learn enough about the functionalities of the ESP32 camera module to implement a motion tracking feature on my project.

- With this video in particular, "MAKE a DIY Security Camera with ESP32-CAM", I was able to apply similar concepts to my project. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GNP_wO85WBY

- Concepts applied:
    - Assembly
    - Uploading software onto the ESP32-CAM
    - Accessing the stream

Application: How did you apply this to your final project?

- I applied a similar cam feature to my project but for motion detection, I projected the stream onto my laptop and uploaded C++ code for ESP32 control from my Arduino IDE. I created my motion tracking software through Python.

